<h1>Problem 2111 - 2010 Iran TST, P5 of 12, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>Circles \(W_1,W_2\) intersect at \(P,K\). \(XY\) is common tangent of two circles which is nearer to \(P\) and \(X\) is on \(W_1\) and \(Y\) is on \(W_2\). \(XP\) intersects \(W_2\) for the second time in \(C\) and \(YP\) intersects \(W_1\) in \(B\). Let \(A\) be intersection point of \(BX\) and \(CY\). Prove that if \(Q\) is the second intersection point of circumcircles of \(ABC\) and \(AXY\)
\[\angle QXA=\angle QKP\]</p>
